Step 1: Create a MongoDB Atlas Account

      Go to 👉 https://www.mongodb.com/cloud/atlas
      Click "Try Free" or "Sign In".
      Sign up using Google or email.

🏗 Step 2: Create a Free Cluster

      After login, click “Create” → “Deploy a Database”.     
      Select Free Shared (M0) tier.      
      Choose a cloud provider (AWS / Azure / GCP) and nearest region.      
      Click Create Deployment.
      ⏳ Wait for a few minutes until your cluster is ready.

🔑 Step 3: Create a Database User

      In the Database Deployment Dashboard, click Database Access.
      Click “Add New Database User”.

Choose Password authentication.

Set:

      Username: admin
      Password: something secure
      Click Add User.

🌍 Step 4: Allow Network Access

      Go to Network Access → Add IP Address.
      Click Add Access from Anywhere (0.0.0.0/0) → Confirm.
      This allows connections from your computer for testing.

🔗 Step 5: Get the Connection String

      Go back to Database Deployments.   
      Click Connect → Connect your application.      
      Choose Python and version 3.4 or later.      
      Copy the connection string — it looks like:
      mongodb+srv://admin:<password>@cluster0.mongodb.net/?retryWrites=true&w=majority

🧠 Step 6: Install the MongoDB Python Driver

In your terminal:

pip install pymongo
python test.py

from pymongo import MongoClient

# Replace <password> with your actual password
uri = "mongodb+srv://admin:<password>@cluster0.mongodb.net/?retryWrites=true&w=majority"

client = MongoClient(uri)
db = client['testDB']
collection = db['users']

# Insert data
collection.insert_one({"name": "Alice", "email": "alice@example.com"})

# Fetch and display all documents
for user in collection.find():
    print(user)
